The paper focuses on the development of a visual navigation engine for autonomous nano-UAVs, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) categories. The use of deep learning algorithms and the development of a novel methodology for their deployment suggest that the paper may also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the paper's focus on real-time execution and responsiveness suggests that it may also fall under the systems and control (cs.SY) category.
